enum ITC_KEYBOARD::CUsbKeyTypes::usbFlagsHigh

Bit flags controlling the extra attriutes of the key mapping.

Enumerator:
NoFlag 
StickyOnce  Bit 16: 01,00,00: Sticky Once (Key remains pressed until next key press of any
StickyPersist  Bit 17: 02,00,00: Sticky Persist (Key remains pressed until next key press of same key)
StickyLock  Bit 18: 04,00,00: Sticky Lock (Key pressed twice in a row remains pressed until next key press of same key. Otherwise behaves like Sticky Once.)
Reserved1  Bit 19: 08,00,00: Reserved
LED1  Bit 20: 10,00,00: LED 1 (Key lights CAPS LOCK LED when depressed)
LED2  Bit 21: 20,00,00: LED 2 (Key lights NUM LOCK LED when depressed)
LED3  Bit 22: 40,00,00: LED 3 (Key lights SCOLL LOCK LED when depressed)
Reserved  Bit 23: 80,00,00: Reserved

enum ITC_KEYBOARD::CUsbKeyTypes::usbFlagsLow

Bit flags controlling the main type of the key mapping.

Enumerator:
NormalKey 
ShiftKeyIndex  Bit 0: 00,00,01: Shift Key Index (Changes Shift planes).
NamedEventIndex  Bit 1: 00,00,02: Named Event Index (Sets/Resets a Named Event Level based on Key State and Sets a Named Event at every Key State Change)
MultiKeyIndex  Bit 2: 00,00,04: MultiKey Index(Single key press emulates multiple key strokes)
ModifierIndex  Bit 3: 00,00,08: Modifier Index (Shift/Control/Alt/Caps/etc.)
AppLaunchKey  Bit 4: 00,00,10: App Launch (Microsoft Shell Application Launch Key)
FunctionKeyIndex  Bit 5: 00,00,20: Function Key Index (Launches a specified function from a DLL)
RotateKeyIndex  Bit 6: 00,00,40: Rotate Key Index (Key that cycles through a specific set of keys)
Reserved  Bit 7: 00,00,40: Reserved

enum ITC_KEYBOARD::CUsbKeyTypes::usbFlagsMid

Bit flags controlling the additional attributes of the key mapping.

Enumerator:
NoFlag 
Extended  Bit 8: 00,01,00: Extended Key )PC Scan Code is accompanied by the Extended 0xE0 Byte)
NoRepeat  Bit 9: 00,02,00: Non Repeating (Key does not Auto Repeat)
Silent  Bit 10: 00,04,00: Silent (No key click).
VKEY  Bit 11: 00,08,00: VKEY (No Scan Code-vkey translation)
NOOP  Bit 12: 00,10,00: Ignored (NOOP key).
Shifted  Bit 13: 00,20,00: Shifted (Sends Shift before key).
NoChord  Bit 14: 00,40,00: No Chord (Only for multikeys).
Reserved  Bit 15: 00,80,00: Reserved
